This article is a letter from President Barack Obama to the Speaker of the House regarding the designation of contingent emergency funding for the 2009-H1N1 influenza outbreak. The letter states that Congress has appropriated $7.65 billion to the Department of Health and Human Services for the outbreak, including a $5.8 billion contingent appropriation for a pandemic. The President has designated $1.825 billion of the contingent appropriation as emergency funds for critical needs related to emerging influenza viruses. Additionally, he has designated an additional $2.716 billion to support various departments in procuring vaccine products and supplies, antiviral medications, and preparations for a vaccination campaign. The severity of the outbreak in the upcoming flu season remains uncertain, and decisions regarding the national response will be based on the results of clinical trials and the latest information about the virus. The President concludes by stating that further communication will be made if additional funds are required.